title: Staph infection forces Giants to place tight end Daniel Fells on injured reserve
text:
Staph infection forces Giants to place tight end Daniel Fells on injured reserve THE ASSOCIATED PRESS First Posted: October 05, 2015 - 12:42 pmLast Updated: October 05, 2015 - 12:43 pm We also have more stories about: (click the phrases to see a list) 
People: 
EAST RUTHERFORD, New Jersey â€” The New York Giants are planning to place tight end Daniel Fells on injured reserve after discovering that he has a staph infection. 
The Giants announced their plans Monday. 
Fells has been bothered by an ankle injury in recent weeks and missed Sunday's win over the Buffalo Bills. In evaluating the injury, it was discovered that he has a staph infection, which requires treatment. 
With tight end Jerome Cunningham sidelined with a knee injury, the Giants signed Will Tye off their practice squad Saturday.
